The body of a 70-year-old man was found decomposing in his house at Mtongwe area, Mombasa.The man was last seen at his private clinic on October 27.Likoni police boss Willy Simba said the man had lived in the area for more than 20 years and was staying alone."There were no physical injuries on the body," Simba said, adding that police are investigating the matter.He said neighbours reported a foul smell from the man's house after which police discovered the body.The deceased has been taken to Coast General Hospital for postmortem.